
  Name:  lround
 
  #include <math.h>
  long int lroundf(float arg);
  long int lround(double arg);
  long int lroundl(long double arg);

  The lround( ) family of functions returns the value of arg
  rounded to the nearest long integer.Values precisely between two
  values, such as 3.5, are rounded up.lround( ), lroundf( ), and 
  lroundl( ) were added by C99.
 
  Related Functions: llround and round

